  "parent": "pt-BR",
  "notes": "Paulistano (São Paulo city / São Paulo State urban variety). Reference variety of Barbosa & Albano (2004, JIPA). Inherits the pt-BR base unchanged: full /t,d/ -> [t͡ʃ,d͡ʒ] before [i,ɪ]; strong onset /r/ -> [ʁ~x~h]; coda /R/ tap [ɾ] preferred (NOT retroflex), drops word-finally in infinitives; coda /S/ stays alveolar [s,z] by voicing assimilation (NO chiado); coda /l/ -> [w]; post-stressed and word-final reduction [ɪ ʊ ɐ]; /ɲ/ frequently -> [j̃]; word-initial pretonic /eN/ -> [ĩ] (então -> [ĩˈtɐ̃w̃]). Prestige standard of southeastern media alongside Carioca. The retroflex 'r caipira' described by Amaral (1920) §6b belongs to the surrounding caipira interior (pt-BR-x-caipira), NOT to the São Paulo capital variety modelled here — coda /r/ is a plain tap [ɾ].",
  "quality": "research",
  "script_type": "alphabet",
